data.name: bufferbyteDD.ToolTip
data.value: The limit on how much data the program is allowed to temporarily hold in memory (buffer) before it gets processed or saved. Less BufferByte consume less memory but may slow down the downloading. Higher BufferByte consume more memory. Do Not Change If you usually download multiple files at once. It will slow down your system very much.

data.name: maxparallelchunks.ToolTip
data.value: It definies how many chunks can run downloading task at same time. More chunks can download file more faster but may consume more memory. Maximum Parallel Chunks cannot be more than File Download Chunks.

data.name: maxchunks.ToolTip
data.value: Instead of downloading the entire file at once, the file is split into smaller pieces (chunks). Each chunk is downloaded individually and reassembled to form the complete file. Higher value of Chunks can increase download speed but may consume more memory. Higher chunks is Not Recommended if you download multiple files.

data.name: Label19.Text
data.value: Aura Downloader is a comprehensive file download manager designed for efficiency and ease of use. It enables users to search and download video or audio directly from YouTube and SoundCloud. Additionally, it offers a custom file download feature, allowing users to retrieve any file by pasting a direct download link. With a streamlined interface and reliable performance, Aura Downloader simplifies the downloading process.
